{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775876214741,"sessionID":"ses_28587d457ffe7m7yY507WED0aS","part":{"id":"prt_d7a788f8b001SBpy5b1i0ZqzId","messageID":"msg_d7a78792e001Wp1P5fQQhVbR20","sessionID":"ses_28587d457ffe7m7yY507WED0aS","type":"tool","tool":"glob","callID":"toolu_tool-72d205c906664d24985bde40ad66b1dd","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"pattern":"**/agentcube/**/*.py"},"output":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/__init__.py\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/cmd/cli/agentcube/__init__.py\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/cmd/cli/agentcube/cli/main.py\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/status_runtime.py\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/invoke_runtime.py\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/publish_runtime.py\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/cmd/cli/agentcube/services/__init__.py\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/cmd/cli/agentcube/services/agentcube_provider.py\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/cmd/cli/agentcube/services/k8s_provider.py\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/build_runtime.py\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/cmd/cli/agentcube/services/docker_service.py\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/pack_runtime.py\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/cmd/cli/agentcube/services/metadata_service.py\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/cmd/cli/agentcube/models/pack_models.py\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/cmd/cli/agentcube/models/__init__.py\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/cmd/cli/agentcube/cli/__init__.py","metadata":{"count":16,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z","time":{"start":1775876214705,"end":1775876214740}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775876214779,"sessionID":"ses_28587d457ffe7m7yY507WED0aS","part":{"id":"prt_d7a788a7f0017iCyHgMGZm3I0H","messageID":"msg_d7a78792e001Wp1P5fQQhVbR20","sessionID":"ses_28587d457ffe7m7yY507WED0aS","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-b498e3e50c434e99a4af8da230edd1b1","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-024/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-024/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-024 — DockerService 封装 Design\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: | Item | Value |\n6: |------|-------|\n7: | AR | AR-024 — DockerService 封装 |\n8: | Module | `cmd/cli` |\n9: | Language | Python |\n10: | Size | M |\n11: | Stage | ST-1 |\n12: \n13: `DockerService` encapsulates Docker SDK operations for container image lifecycle management: availability checks, image building, metadata retrieval, registry push with authentication, and image removal. It provides a clean abstraction layer between CLI runtime classes and the Docker Python SDK.\n14: \n15: ---\n16: \n17: ## Architecture\n18: \n19: ### System Context\n20: \n21: ```\n22: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n23: │                         User CLI                                 │\n24: │  kubectl-agentcube build -f ./agent                             │\n25: │  kubectl-agentcube publish -f ./agent                           │\n26: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n27:                                │\n28:                                ▼\n29: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n30: │                     Runtime Layer                                │\n31: │  ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐   │\n32: │  │ BuildRuntime                                              │   │\n33: │  │  - build() → calls DockerService.build_image()            │   │\n34: │  │  - _validate_prerequisites() → check_docker_available()   │   │\n35: │  └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘   │\n36: │  ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐   │\n37: │  │ PublishRuntime                                             │   │\n38: │  │  - _prepare_local_image() → DockerService.push_image()    │   │\n39: │  └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘   │\n40: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n41:                                │\n42:                                ▼\n43: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n44: │                    DockerService                                 │\n45: │  ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐   │\n46: │  │ DockerService(verbose=False)                              │   │\n47: │  │  - _client: Any (lazy-loaded DockerClient)                │   │\n48: │  │  - check_docker_available() → bool                        │   │\n49: │  │  - build_image(...) → Dict[str, Any]                      │   │\n50: │  │  - get_image_info(...) → Dict[str, Any]                   │   │\n51: │  │  - push_image(...) → Dict[str, Any]                       │   │\n52: │  │  - remove_image(...) → bool                               │   │\n53: │  │  - _format_size(bytes) → str                              │   │\n54: │  │  - _get_client() → DockerClient                           │   │\n55: │  │  - build_image_legacy(...) → Dict[str, Any]               │   │\n56: │  └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘   │\n57: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n58:                                │\n59:                                ▼\n60: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n61: │                    Docker Python SDK                             │\n62: │  ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐   │\n63: │  │ docker.from_env() → DockerClient                          │   │\n64: │  │  - client.ping() → bool                                   │   │\n65: │  │  - client.images.build(...) → (Image, logs)               │   │\n66: │  │  - client.images.get(name) → Image                        │   │\n67: │  │  - client.images.push(name) → logs                        │   │\n68: │  │  - client.images.remove(name) → None                      │   │\n69: │  │  - client.login(...) → None                               │   │\n70: │  └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐   │\n71: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n72:                                │\n73:                                ▼\n74: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n75: │                    Docker Daemon (dockerd)                       │\n76: │  ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐   │\n77: │  │ Docker Engine API                                          │   │\n78: │  │  - /_ping                                                  │   │\n79: │  │  - /build                                                  │   │\n80: │  │  - /images/{name}/json                                     │   │\n81: │  │  - /images/{name}/push                                     │   │\n82: │  │  - /images/{name} (DELETE)                                 │   │\n83: │  └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘   │\n84: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n85: ```\n86: \n87: ### Component Diagram\n88: \n89: ```\n90: ┌────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n91: │                         agentcube/services/                         │\n92: ├────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n93: │                                                                     │\n94: │  ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐  │\n95: │  │                    DockerService                              │  │\n96: │  ├──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤  │\n97: │  │ Instance Fields:                                              │  │\n98: │  │   - verbose: bool                                             │  │\n99: │  │   - _client: Any (private, lazy-loaded)                       │  │\n100: │  │                                                               │  │\n101: │  │ Public Methods:                                               │  │\n102: │  │   + check_docker_available() → bool                          │  │\n103: │  │   + build_image(dockerfile_path, context_path,                │  │\n104: │  │                  image_name, tag, build_args, verbose)        │  │\n105: │  │     → Dict[str, Any]                                          │  │\n106: │  │   + get_image_info(image_name, tag) → Dict[str, Any]         │  │\n107: │  │   + push_image(image_name, registry_url,                     │  │\n108: │  │                 username, password) → Dict[str, Any]         │  │\n109: │  │   + remove_image(image_name) → bool                           │  │\n110: │  │                                                               │  │\n111: │  │ Private Methods:                                              │  │\n112: │  │   - _get_client() → Any                                      │  │\n113: │  │   - _format_size(size_bytes: int) → str                      │  │\n114: │  │                                                               │  │\n115: │  │ Legacy Method:                                                │  │\n116: │  │   + build_image_legacy(workspace_path, metadata,             │  │\n117: │  │                        tag, buildargs) → Dict[str, Any]       │  │\n118: │  └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘  │\n119: │                                                                     │\n120: └────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n121: ```\n122: \n123: ### Request Flow\n124: \n125: ```\n126: BuildRuntime.build()\n127:          │\n128:          ▼\n129: DockerService.check_docker_available()\n130:          │\n131:          ├─ docker.from_env() → client\n132:          ├─ client.ping() → True/False\n133:          │\n134:          ▼\n135: DockerService.build_image(\n136:     dockerfile_path=Path(\"./Dockerfile\"),\n137:     context_path=Path(\"./workspace\"),\n138:     image_name=\"my-agent\",\n139:     tag=\"v1.0.0\",\n140:     build_args={\"HTTP_PROXY\": \"http://proxy:8080\"},\n141:     verbose=True\n142: )\n143:          │\n144:          ├─ _get_client() → client (lazy load)\n145:          ├─ time.time() → start_time\n146:          ├─ client.images.build(\n147:          │      path=str(context_path),\n148:          │      dockerfile=str(dockerfile_path),\n149:          │      tag=f\"{image_name}:{tag}\",\n150:          │      buildargs=build_args\n151:          │  ) → (Image, build_logs)\n152:          ├─ [if verbose] stream build_logs\n153:          ├─ time.time() → build_time\n154:          ├─ image.attrs[\"Size\"] → size_bytes\n155:          ├─ _format_size(size_bytes) → \"125.3 MB\"\n156:          │\n157:          ▼\n158: Return Dict:\n159: {\n160:     \"image_name\": \"my-agent\",\n161:     \"image_id\": \"sha256:abc123...\",\n162:     \"image_size\": \"125.3 MB\",\n163:     \"build_time\": 45.2,\n164:     \"tag\": \"v1.0.0\"\n165: }\n166: ```\n167: \n168: ---\n169: \n170: ## Data Structures\n171: \n172: ### BuildImageResult\n173: \n174: ```python\n175: BuildImageResult = TypedDict(\"BuildImageResult\", {\n176:     \"image_name\": str,       # Image name without tag\n177:     \"image_id\": str,         # Docker image ID (sha256:...)\n178:     \"image_size\": str,       # Human-readable size (e.g., \"125.3 MB\")\n179:     \"build_time\": float,     # Build duration in seconds\n180:     \"tag\": str,              # Image tag (e.g., \"v1.0.0\" or \"latest\")\n181: })\n182: ```\n183: \n184: ### GetImageInfoResult\n185: \n186: ```python\n187: GetImageInfoResult = TypedDict(\"GetImageInfoResult\", {\n188:     \"image_id\": str,         # Docker image ID (sha256:...)\n189:     \"image_size\": str,       # Human-readable size\n190: })\n191: ```\n192: \n193: ### PushImageResult\n194: \n195: ```python\n196: PushImageResult = TypedDict(\"PushImageResult\", {\n197:     \"pushed_image\": str,     # Full image name with registry URL\n198:     \"push_time\": float,      # Push duration in seconds\n199: })\n200: ```\n201: \n202: ### Size Format Thresholds\n203: \n204: | Range | Format | Example |\n205: |-------|--------|---------|\n206: | `< 1024` | `\"{n} B\"` | `\"500 B\"` |\n207: | `< 1024*1024` | `\"{n/1024:.1f} KB\"` | `\"1.0 KB\"` |\n208: | `< 1024*1024*1024` | `\"{n/(1024*1024):.1f} MB\"` | `\"1.0 MB\"` |\n209: | `>= 1024*1024*1024` | `\"{n/(1024*1024*1024):.1f} GB\"` | `\"1.0 GB\"` |\n210: \n211: ---\n212: \n213: ## API Contracts\n214: \n215: ### check_docker_available()\n216: \n217: ```python\n218: def check_docker_available(self) -> bool:\n219:     \"\"\"\n220:     Check if Docker daemon is running and accessible.\n221:     \n222:     Implementation:\n223:         - Import docker SDK\n224:         - Create client from environment (docker.from_env())\n225:         - Call client.ping()\n226:         \n227:     Returns:\n228:         True if Docker is available, False otherwise.\n229:     \n230:     Note:\n231:         Catches all exceptions and returns False (no exception propagation).\n232:         Used for prerequisite validation in build/publish commands.\n233:     \"\"\"\n234: ```\n235: \n236: ### build_image()\n237: \n238: ```python\n239: def build_image(\n240:     self,\n241:     dockerfile_path: Path,\n242:     context_path: Path,\n243:     image_name: str,\n244:     tag: Optional[str] = \"latest\",\n245:     build_args: Optional[Dict[str, str]] = None,\n246:     verbose: bool = False,\n247: ) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n248:     \"\"\"\n249:     Build Docker image using Docker SDK.\n250:     \n251:     Args:\n252:         dockerfile_path: Path to Dockerfile\n253:         context_path: Build context directory\n254:         image_name: Image name without tag\n255:         tag: Image tag (default: \"latest\")\n256:         build_args: Optional build arguments (e.g., {\"HTTP_PROXY\": url})\n257:         verbose: Stream build logs to stdout\n258:     \n259:     Returns:\n260:         Dict containing:\n261:             - image_name: str (name without tag)\n262:             - image_id: str (sha256 digest)\n263:             - image_size: str (human-readable)\n264:             - build_time: float (seconds)\n265:             - tag: str\n266:     \n267:     Raises:\n268:         docker.errors.BuildError: If build fails\n269:         docker.errors.APIError: If Docker API error\n270:         Exception: Any other error (propagated with context)\n271:     \n272:     Implementation:\n273:         - Uses client.images.build() with path, dockerfile, tag, buildargs\n274:         - Measures elapsed time with time.time()\n275:         - Streams logs if verbose=True\n276:         - Formats size with _format_size()\n277:     \"\"\"\n278: ```\n279: \n280: ### get_image_info()\n281: \n282: ```python\n283: def get_image_info(self, image_name: str, tag: str = \"latest\") -> Dict[str, Any]:\n284:     \"\"\"\n285:     Retrieve image metadata from Docker.\n286:     \n287:     Args:\n288:         image_name: Image name without tag\n289:         tag: Image tag (default: \"latest\")\n290:     \n291:     Returns:\n292:         Dict containing:\n293:             - image_id: str (sha256 digest)\n294:             - image_size: str (human-readable)\n295:     \n296:     Raises:\n297:         docker.errors.ImageNotFound: If image not found\n298:         Exception: Any other error (propagated)\n299:     \n300:     Note:\n301:         Full name constructed as f\"{image_name}:{tag}\"\n302:         Uses client.images.get(full_name)\n303:     \"\"\"\n304: ```\n305: \n306: ### push_image()\n307: \n308: ```python\n309: def push_image(\n310:     self,\n311:     image_name: str,\n312:     registry_url: Optional[str] = None,\n313:     username: Optional[str] = None,\n314:     password: Optional[str] = None,\n315: ) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n316:     \"\"\"\n317:     Push Docker image to registry.\n318:     \n319:     Args:\n320:         image_name: Full image name (may include tag)\n321:         registry_url: Optional registry URL (prepended to image_name)\n322:         username: Registry username (for login)\n323:         password: Registry password (for login)\n324:     \n325:     Returns:\n326:         Dict containing:\n327:             - pushed_image: str (full image name with registry)\n328:             - push_time: float (seconds)\n329:     \n330:     Implementation:\n331:         1. If username/password/registry_url provided:\n332:            - client.login(username, password, registry=registry_url)\n333:         2. Construct full image name:\n334:            - If registry_url: f\"{registry_url}/{image_name}\"\n335:            - Else: image_name\n336:         3. client.images.push(full_image_name)\n337:         4. Measure elapsed time\n338:     \n339:     Note:\n340:         Login is optional; assumes pre-authenticated Docker if credentials omitted.\n341:         Push logs are not streamed (may be extended in future).\n342:     \"\"\"\n343: ```\n344: \n345: ### remove_image()\n346: \n347: ```python\n348: def remove_image(self, image_name: str) -> bool:\n349:     \"\"\"\n350:     Remove Docker image from local daemon.\n351:     \n352:     Args:\n353:         image_name: Full image name (may include tag)\n354:     \n355:     Returns:\n356:         True if removal succeeded, False on any error.\n357:     \n358:     Note:\n359:         Does not propagate exceptions; logs warning if verbose.\n360:         Used for cleanup in error recovery scenarios.\n361:     \"\"\"\n362: ```\n363: \n364: ### _get_client() (Private)\n365: \n366: ```python\n367: def _get_client(self) -> Any:\n368:     \"\"\"\n369:     Lazy-load Docker client instance.\n370:     \n371:     Returns:\n372:         DockerClient from docker.from_env()\n373:     \n374:     Note:\n375:         Client cached in self._client for reuse.\n376:         Import docker inside method (lazy import).\n377:     \"\"\"\n378: ```\n379: \n380: ### _format_size() (Private)\n381: \n382: ```python\n383: def _format_size(self, size_bytes: int) -> str:\n384:     \"\"\"\n385:     Convert byte count to human-readable string.\n386:     \n387:     Args:\n388:         size_bytes: Size in bytes\n389:     \n390:     Returns:\n391:         Human-readable size string (e.g., \"125.3 MB\")\n392:     \n393:     Thresholds:\n394:         - Bytes: < 1024\n395:         - KB: < 1024*1024\n396:         - MB: < 1024*1024*1024\n397:         - GB: >= 1024*1024*1024\n398:     \"\"\"\n399: ```\n400: \n401: ### build_image_legacy() (Legacy)\n402: \n403: ```python\n404: def build_image_legacy(\n405:     self,\n406:     workspace_path: Path,\n407:     metadata: AgentMetadata,\n408:     tag: Optional[str] = None,\n409:     buildargs: Optional[Dict[str, str]] = None,\n410: ) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n411:     \"\"\"\n412:     Legacy build method for backward compatibility.\n413:     \n414:     Args:\n415:         workspace_path: Path to workspace (contains Dockerfile)\n416:         metadata: AgentMetadata with agent_name, version\n417:         tag: Override tag (uses metadata.version or \"latest\")\n418:         buildargs: Build arguments\n419:     \n420:     Returns:\n421:         Same as build_image()\n422:     \n423:     Note:\n424:         Delegates to build_image() with derived parameters:\n425:         - dockerfile_path = workspace_path / \"Dockerfile\"\n426:         - context_path = workspace_path\n427:         - image_name = metadata.agent_name\n428:         - tag = tag or metadata.version or \"latest\"\n429:     \"\"\"\n430: ```\n431: \n432: ---\n433: \n434: ## Error Handling\n435: \n436: ### Error Categories\n437: \n438: | Category | Condition | Action | Propagated? |\n439: |----------|-----------|--------|-------------|\n440: | Docker Unavailable | `docker.from_env()` fails or `ping()` fails | Return `False` | No (swallowed) |\n441: | Build Failure | `client.images.build()` raises | Print verbose message, raise | Yes |\n442: | Image Not Found | `client.images.get()` fails | Print verbose message, raise | Yes |\n443: | Push Failure | `client.images.push()` raises | Raise exception | Yes |\n444: | Login Failure | `client.login()` raises | Propagate | Yes |\n445: | Remove Failure | `client.images.remove()` raises | Log warning, return `False` | No |\n446: | Generic SDK Error | Any `docker.errors.*` | Propagate with context | Yes |\n447: \n448: ### Exception Types\n449: \n450: | Exception | Source | Handling |\n451: |-----------|--------|----------|\n452: | `docker.errors.BuildError` | `build_image()` | Propagate; caller handles |\n453: | `docker.errors.APIError` | Any SDK call | Propagate |\n454: | `docker.errors.ImageNotFound` | `get_image_info()` | Propagate |\n455: | `Exception` (generic) | Any method | Propagate or swallow based on method |\n456: \n457: ### Verbose Logging\n458: \n459: ```python\n460: # check_docker_available: no verbose output\n461: # build_image: verbose streams build logs\n462: if verbose:\n463:     for log in build_logs:\n464:         if \"stream\" in log:\n465:             print(log[\"stream\"].strip())\n466: \n467: # get_image_info: verbose prints error\n468: if self.verbose:\n469:     print(f\"Error getting image info: {e}\")\n470: raise\n471: \n472: # build_image failure: verbose prints timing\n473: if verbose:\n474:     print(f\"Build failed after {build_time:.1f}s: {e}\")\n475: raise\n476: \n477: # remove_image: verbose would log warning (currently silent)\n478: ```\n479: \n480: ---\n481: \n482: ## Testing Strategy\n483: \n484: ### Unit Tests\n485: \n486: | Test File | Coverage |\n487: |-----------|----------|\n488: | `tests/test_docker_service.py` | All DockerService methods |\n489: \n490: ### Test Cases\n491: \n492: #### Initialization Tests\n493: \n494: | Test Case | Scenario | Expected |\n495: |-----------|----------|----------|\n496: | `test_init_default_verbose` | `DockerService()` | `verbose == False` |\n497: | `test_init_verbose_true` | `DockerService(verbose=True)` | `verbose == True` |\n498: \n499: #### check_docker_available Tests\n500: \n501: | Test Case | Scenario | Expected |\n502: |-----------|----------|----------|\n503: | `test_docker_available` | Mock `docker.from_env()` → ping returns True | Returns `True` |\n504: | `test_docker_unavailable` | Mock `docker.from_env()` raises Exception | Returns `False` |\n505: \n506: #### _format_size Tests\n507: \n508: | Test Case | Input | Expected |\n509: |-----------|-------|----------|\n510: | `test_format_size_bytes` | `500` | `\"500 B\"` |\n511: | `test_format_size_kb` | `1024` | `\"1.0 KB\"` |\n512: | `test_format_size_mb` | `1048576` | `\"1.0 MB\"` |\n513: | `test_format_size_gb` | `1073741824` | `\"1.0 GB\"` |\n514: | `test_format_size_large_mb` | `125300000` | `\"~119.3 MB\"` |\n515: \n516: #### get_image_info Tests\n517: \n518: | Test Case | Scenario | Expected |\n519: |-----------|----------|----------|\n520: | `test_get_image_info_success` | Mock client.images.get() returns image | Dict with `image_id`, `image_size` |\n521: | `test_get_image_info_not_found` | Mock raises \"Image not found\" | Exception raised |\n522: \n523: #### build_image Tests\n524: \n525: | Test Case | Scenario | Expected |\n526: |-----------|----------|----------|\n527: | `test_build_image_basic` | Mock build returns image | Dict with all fields, correct tag |\n528: | `test_build_image_with_proxy` | Pass build_args with HTTP_PROXY | Build called with buildargs |\n529: | `test_build_image_default_tag` | No tag specified | Tag defaults to \"latest\" |\n530: | `test_build_image_failure` | Mock build raises Exception | Exception raised, verbose printed |\n531: \n532: #### push_image Tests\n533: \n534: | Test Case | Scenario | Expected |\n535: |-----------|----------|----------|\n536: | `test_push_image_basic` | No registry/credentials | `pushed_image` == input name |\n537: | `test_push_image_with_registry` | registry_url provided | `pushed_image` includes registry |\n538: | `test_push_image_with_auth` | username/password provided | `client.login()` called |\n539: \n540: #### remove_image Tests\n541: \n542: | Test Case | Scenario | Expected |\n543: |-----------|----------|----------|\n544: | `test_remove_image_success` | Mock remove succeeds | Returns `True` |\n545: | `test_remove_image_failure` | Mock remove raises Exception | Returns `False` |\n546: \n547: ### Mock Strategy\n548: \n549: ```python\n550: # Docker client mock pattern\n551: @pytest.fixture\n552: def mock_docker_client():\n553:     with patch('docker.from_env') as mock_docker:\n554:         mock_client = MagicMock()\n555:         mock_client.ping.return_value = True\n556:         mock_client.images.build.return_value = (mock_image, [])\n557:         mock_client.images.get.return_value = mock_image\n558:         mock_client.images.push.return_value = []\n559:         mock_client.images.remove.return_value = None\n560:         mock_client.login.return_value = None\n561:         mock_docker.return_value = mock_client\n562:         yield mock_client\n563: \n564: # Image mock\n565: @pytest.fixture\n566: def mock_image():\n567:     image = MagicMock()\n568:     image.id = \"sha256:abc123def456\"\n569:     image.attrs = {\"Size\": 125300000}\n570:     return image\n571: \n572: # _get_client override pattern\n573: with patch.object(service, '_get_client') as mock_get:\n574:     mock_get.return_value = mock_client\n575: ```\n576: \n577: ---\n578: \n579: ## File Structure\n580: \n581: ```\n582: cmd/cli/\n583: ├── agentcube/\n584: │   └── services/\n585: │       ├── __init__.py              # Services package marker\n586: │       ├── metadata_service.py      # AgentMetadata, MetadataService\n587: │       ├── docker_service.py        # DockerService (AR-024)\n588: │       ├── k8s_provider.py          # KubernetesProvider (future)\n589: │       └── agentcube_provider.py    # AgentCubeProvider (future)\n590: └── tests/\n591:     ├── test_docker_service.py       # DockerService unit tests\n592:     ├── test_build_runtime.py        # BuildRuntime (uses DockerService)\n593:     └── test_publish_runtime.py      # PublishRuntime (uses DockerService)\n594: ```\n595: \n596: ---\n597: \n598: ## Dependencies\n599: \n600: ### Runtime Dependencies\n601: \n602: | Package | Version | Purpose |\n603: |---------|---------|---------|\n604: | `docker` | `>=6.0.0` | Docker SDK for Python; client.from_env(), images API |\n605: | `typing` | (stdlib) | Optional, Dict, Any type hints |\n606: | `pathlib` | (stdlib) | Path for file path handling |\n607: | `time` | (stdlib) | time.time() for duration measurement |\n608: \n609: ### pyproject.toml Entry\n610: \n611: ```toml\n612: [project]\n613: dependencies = [\n614:     \"docker>=6.0.0\",\n615:     ...\n616: ]\n617: ```\n618: \n619: ---\n620: \n621: ## Implementation Notes\n622: \n623: ### Lazy Client Loading\n624: \n625: ```python\n626: def _get_client(self) -> Any:\n627:     \"\"\"\n628:     Docker client is lazily loaded on first use.\n629:     \n630:     Benefits:\n631:     - Avoids import error at module load if docker SDK unavailable\n632:     - Single client instance reused across multiple operations\n633:     - Allows check_docker_available() to test SDK availability separately\n634:     \"\"\"\n635:     import docker\n636:     if self._client is None:\n637:         self._client = docker.from_env()\n638:     return self._client\n639: ```\n640: \n641: ### Size Formatting Thresholds\n642: \n643: | Threshold | Calculation | Example |\n644: |-----------|-------------|---------|\n645: | Bytes | `size_bytes < 1024` | `500 → \"500 B\"` |\n646: | KB | `size_bytes < 1024*1024` | `2048 → \"2.0 KB\"` |\n647: | MB | `size_bytes < 1024*1024*1024` | `5242880 → \"5.0 MB\"` |\n648: | GB | `size_bytes >= 1024*1024*1024` | `2147483648 → \"2.0 GB\"` |\n649: \n650: ### Build Args Convention\n651: \n652: ```python\n653: # Proxy build arguments passed to Dockerfile\n654: build_args = {\n655:     \"HTTP_PROXY\": \"http://proxy.example.com:8080\",\n656:     \"HTTPS_PROXY\": \"http://proxy.example.com:8080\",\n657: }\n658: \n659: # Dockerfile must ARG these:\n660: # ARG HTTP_PROXY\n661: # ARG HTTPS_PROXY\n662: ```\n663: \n664: ### Registry URL Construction\n665: \n666: ```python\n667: # Prepend registry URL to image name\n668: if registry_url:\n669:     full_image_name = f\"{registry_url}/{image_name}\"\n670: else:\n671:     full_image_name = image_name\n672: \n673: # Example:\n674: # image_name = \"my-agent:latest\"\n675: # registry_url = \"registry.example.com\"\n676: # → full_image_name = \"registry.example.com/my-agent:latest\"\n677: ```\n678: \n679: ### Verbose Build Streaming\n680: \n681: ```python\n682: # Build logs streamed line-by-line\n683: for log in build_logs:\n684:     if \"stream\" in log:\n685:         print(log[\"stream\"].strip())\n686: \n687: # Example log format:\n688: # {\"stream\": \"Step 1/5 : FROM python:3.10-slim\\n\"}\n689: # {\"stream\": \" ---> abc123def456\\n\"}\n690: ```\n691: \n692: ---\n693: \n694: ## References\n695: \n696: - cli-toolkit/design.md — CLI toolkit architecture\n697: - cli-toolkit/spec.md — CLI specification (Docker integration requirements)\n698: - Docker SDK Python: https://docker-py.readthedocs.io/en/stable/\n699: - Docker Engine API: https://docs.docker.com/engine/api/\n700: - AR-021 — CLI build command (uses DockerService)\n701: - AR-022 — CLI publish command (uses DockerService.push_image)\n702: - docker.errors module: https://docker-py.readthedocs.io/en/stable/errors.html\n\n(End of file - total 702 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-024 — DockerService 封装 Design\n\n## Overview\n\n| Item | Value |\n|------|-------|\n| AR | AR-024 — DockerService 封装 |\n| Module | `cmd/cli` |\n| Language | Python |\n| Size | M |\n| Stage | ST-1 |\n\n`DockerService` encapsulates Docker SDK operations for container image lifecycle management: availability checks, image building, metadata retrieval, registry push with authentication, and image removal. It provides a clean abstraction layer between CLI runtime classes and the Docker Python SDK.\n\n---\n\n## Architecture\n\n### System Context\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-024/design.md","time":{"start":1775876214695,"end":1775876214776}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775876214787,"sessionID":"ses_28587d457ffe7m7yY507WED0aS","part":{"id":"prt_d7a788e8d001TeCSkeYtAqoUTW","messageID":"msg_d7a78792e001Wp1P5fQQhVbR20","sessionID":"ses_28587d457ffe7m7yY507WED0aS","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-44537de78eef44b386c71fce670b7b50","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-024/tasks.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-024/tasks.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-024 — DockerService 封装 Tasks\n2: \n3: ## Metadata\n4: \n5: | Item | Value |\n6: |------|-------|\n7: | AR | AR-024 — DockerService 封装 |\n8: | Module | `cmd/cli` |\n9: | Language | Python |\n10: | Size | M |\n11: | Design | [Stage ST-3 completed] |\n12: \n13: ---\n14: \n15: ## Task Checklist\n16: \n17: ### Phase 1: Core Implementation (ST-1)\n18: \n19: - [x] **T1.1**: Implement `DockerService.__init__` with verbose flag and `_client=None`\n20:   - Purpose: Constructor initializes verbose flag and lazy client placeholder\n21:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/docker_service.py:9-11`\n22:   - Verification: `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_docker_service.py::TestDockerServiceInit -v`\n23: \n24: - [x] **T1.2**: Implement `_get_client()` lazy-loading method\n25:   - Purpose: Lazy import docker SDK and cache client instance\n26:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/docker_service.py:13-17`\n27:   - Verification: `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_docker_service.py::TestCheckDockerAvailable -v`\n28: \n29: - [x] **T1.3**: Implement `check_docker_available()` method\n30:   - Purpose: Verify Docker daemon connectivity via ping\n31:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/docker_service.py:19-26`\n32:   - Verification: `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_docker_service.py::TestCheckDockerAvailable -v`\n33: \n34: - [x] **T1.4**: Implement `_format_size()` helper method\n35:   - Purpose: Convert byte count to human-readable B/KB/MB/GB string\n36:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/docker_service.py:28-36`\n37:   - Verification: `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_docker_service.py::TestFormatSize -v`\n38: \n39: ### Phase 2: Image Operations (ST-2)\n40: \n41: - [x] **T2.1**: Implement `get_image_info()` method\n42:   - Purpose: Retrieve image metadata (ID, size) from Docker daemon\n43:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/docker_service.py:38-52`\n44:   - Verification: `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_docker_service.py::TestGetImageInfo -v`\n45: \n46: - [x] **T2.2**: Implement `build_image()` method\n47:   - Purpose: Build Docker image with optional build_args and verbose streaming\n48:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/docker_service.py:54-99`\n49:   - Verification: `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_docker_service.py::TestBuildImage -v`\n50: \n51: - [x] **T2.3**: Implement `build_image_legacy()` wrapper\n52:   - Purpose: Provide backward-compatible build with workspace/metadata defaults\n53:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/docker_service.py:101-115`\n54:   - Verification: `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_docker_service.py -k legacy -v`\n55: \n56: - [x] **T2.4**: Implement `push_image()` method\n57:   - Purpose: Push image to registry with optional authentication\n58:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/docker_service.py:117-144`\n59:   - Verification: `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_docker_service.py::TestPushImage -v`\n60: \n61: - [x] **T2.5**: Implement `remove_image()` method\n62:   - Purpose: Remove local image with graceful failure handling\n63:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/docker_service.py:146-152`\n64:   - Verification: `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_docker_service.py::TestRemoveImage -v`\n65: \n66: ### Phase 3: Unit Tests (ST-3)\n67: \n68: - [x] **T3.1**: Write initialization tests\n69:   - Purpose: Verify constructor behavior with verbose flag\n70:   - File: `cmd/cli/tests/test_docker_service.py:9-16`\n71:   - Verification: `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_docker_service.py::TestDockerServiceInit -v`\n72: \n73: - [x] **T3.2**: Write Docker availability tests\n74:   - Purpose: Verify check_docker_available returns True/False correctly\n75:   - File: `cmd/cli/tests/test_docker_service.py:19-31`\n76:   - Verification: `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_docker_service.py::TestCheckDockerAvailable -v`\n77: \n78: - [x] **T3.3**: Write size formatting tests\n79:   - Purpose: Verify _format_size handles B/KB/MB/GB thresholds\n80:   - File: `cmd/cli/tests/test_docker_service.py:34-54`\n81:   - Verification: `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_docker_service.py::TestFormatSize -v`\n82: \n83: - [x] **T3.4**: Write get_image_info tests\n84:   - Purpose: Verify image metadata retrieval and error handling\n85:   - File: `cmd/cli/tests/test_docker_service.py:57-84`\n86:   - Verification: `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_docker_service.py::TestGetImageInfo -v`\n87: \n88: - [x] **T3.5**: Write build_image tests\n89:   - Purpose: Verify build with default/custom tag, build_args, verbose, failure\n90:   - File: `cmd/cli/tests/test_docker_service.py:87-180`\n91:   - Verification: `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_docker_service.py::TestBuildImage -v`\n92: \n93: - [x] **T3.6**: Write push_image tests\n94:   - Purpose: Verify push with registry URL, authentication\n95:   - File: `cmd/cli/tests/test_docker_service.py:183-228`\n96:   - Verification: `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_docker_service.py::TestPushImage -v`\n97: \n98: - [x] **T3.7**: Write remove_image tests\n99:   - Purpose: Verify removal success and graceful failure\n100:   - File: `cmd/cli/tests/test_docker_service.py:230-250`\n101:   - Verification: `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_docker_service.py::TestRemoveImage -v`\n102: \n103: ### Phase 4: Integration Verification (ST-4)\n104: \n105: - [ ] **T4.1**: Verify DockerService integration with BuildRuntime\n106:   - Purpose: Ensure BuildRuntime correctly consumes DockerService.build_image()\n107:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/build_runtime.py`\n108:   - Verification: `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_build_runtime.py -v`\n109: \n110: - [ ] **T4.2**: Verify DockerService integration with PublishRuntime\n111:   - Purpose: Ensure PublishRuntime correctly consumes DockerService.push_image()\n112:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/publish_runtime.py`\n113:   - Verification: `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_publish_runtime.py -v`\n114: \n115: - [ ] **T4.3**: Verify __init__.py exports DockerService\n116:   - Purpose: Ensure DockerService is exported from services package\n117:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/__init__.py`\n118:   - Verification: `python -c \"from agentcube.services import DockerService; print('OK')\"`\n119: \n120: - [ ] **T4.4**: Run full test suite\n121:   - Purpose: Verify all tests pass together\n122:   - File: `cmd/cli/tests/test_docker_service.py`\n123:   - Verification: `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_docker_service.py -v`\n124: \n125: ---\n126: \n127: ## Task Dependencies\n128: \n129: ```\n130: T1.1 (init) ──┬── T1.2 (_get_client)\n131:               │\n132:               ├── T1.3 (check_docker)\n133:               │\n134:               └── T1.4 (_format_size)\n135: \n136: T1.2 + T1.4 ──┬── T2.1 (get_image_info)\n137:               │\n138:               ├── T2.2 (build_image)\n139:               │        │\n140:               │        └── T2.3 (build_image_legacy)\n141:               │\n142:               ├── T2.4 (push_image)\n143:               │\n144:               └── T2.5 (remove_image)\n145: \n146: T2.1-T2.5 ────┬── T3.1-T3.7 (unit tests)\n147:               │\n148:               └── T4.1-T4.4 (integration)\n149: ```\n150: \n151: ---\n152: \n153: ## Verification Commands\n154: \n155: | Task | Verification Command |\n156: |------|----------------------|\n157: | T1.1 | `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_docker_service.py::TestDockerServiceInit -v` |\n158: | T1.2 | `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_docker_service.py::TestCheckDockerAvailable::test_docker_available -v` |\n159: | T1.3 | `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_docker_service.py::TestCheckDockerAvailable -v` |\n160: | T1.4 | `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_docker_service.py::TestFormatSize -v` |\n161: | T2.1 | `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_docker_service.py::TestGetImageInfo -v` |\n162: | T2.2 | `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_docker_service.py::TestBuildImage -v` |\n163: | T2.3 | `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_docker_service.py -k legacy -v` |\n164: | T2.4 | `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_docker_service.py::TestPushImage -v` |\n165: | T2.5 | `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_docker_service.py::TestRemoveImage -v` |\n166: | T3.1-T3.7 | `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_docker_service.py -v` |\n167: | T4.1 | `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_build_runtime.py -v` |\n168: | T4.2 | `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_publish_runtime.py -v` |\n169: | T4.3 | `python -c \"from agentcube.services import DockerService\"` |\n170: | T4.4 | `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_docker_service.py -v` |\n171: \n172: ---\n173: \n174: ## Acceptance Criteria\n175: \n176: - [x] `DockerService.__init__` stores `verbose` and initializes `_client=None`\n177: - [x] `_get_client()` lazy-initializes via `docker.from_env()` and caches result\n178: - [x] `check_docker_available()` returns `True` when daemon responds to ping\n179: - [x] `check_docker_available()` returns `False` on any exception\n180: - [x] `build_image()` calls `client.images.build()` with correct parameters\n181: - [x] `build_image()` returns `{image_name, image_id, image_size, build_time, tag}`\n182: - [x] `build_image()` streams logs when `verbose=True`\n183: - [x] `build_image()` prints failure timing when verbose and exception occurs\n184: - [x] `build_image()` supports `build_args` for proxy configuration\n185: - [x] `get_image_info()` returns `{image_id, image_size}` for existing image\n186: - [x] `get_image_info()` uses `tag=\"latest\"` as default\n187: - [x] `get_image_info()` prints error and re-raises when `verbose=True`\n188: - [x] `_format_size()` formats bytes as B/KB/MB/GB correctly\n189: - [x] `push_image()` constructs full image name with registry URL\n190: - [x] `push_image()` calls `client.login()` when credentials provided\n191: - [x] `push_image()` returns `{pushed_image, push_time}`\n192: - [x] `remove_image()` returns `True` on success, `False` on failure\n193: - [x] `build_image_legacy()` wraps `build_image()` with workspace/metadata defaults\n194: - [x] `build_image_legacy()` uses `metadata.version or \"latest\"` as tag\n195: - [x] `build_image_legacy()` inherits `self.verbose` setting\n196: - [ ] All integration tests with BuildRuntime/PublishRuntime pass\n197: - [ ] DockerService exported from services package\n198: \n199: ---\n200: \n201: ## File Changes Summary\n202: \n203: | File | Action | Lines | Description |\n204: |------|--------|-------|-------------|\n205: | `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/docker_service.py` | Modify | 152 | Core DockerService implementation |\n206: | `cmd/cli/tests/test_docker_service.py` | Modify | 251 | Unit tests for all DockerService methods |\n207: | `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/__init__.py` | Modify | - | Export DockerService |\n208: | `cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/build_runtime.py` | Uses | - | Consumes DockerService.build_image() |\n209: | `cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/publish_runtime.py` | Uses | - | Consumes DockerService.push_image() |\n210: \n211: ---\n212: \n213: ## Implementation Notes\n214: \n215: ### Lazy Client Loading\n216: \n217: The `_get_client()` method uses lazy initialization to avoid import errors at module load time if the docker SDK is unavailable. The client is cached in `_client` for reuse across multiple operations.\n218: \n219: ### Size Formatting Thresholds\n220: \n221: | Threshold | Output Format |\n222: |-----------|---------------|\n223: | `< 1024` | `\"{n} B\"` |\n224: | `< 1024²` | `\"{n/1024:.1f} KB\"` |\n225: | `< 1024³` | `\"{n/1024²:.1f} MB\"` |\n226: | `>= 1024³` | `\"{n/1024³:.1f} GB\"` |\n227: \n228: ### Verbose Build Streaming\n229: \n230: When `verbose=True`, build logs are streamed line-by-line:\n231: ```python\n232: for log in build_logs:\n233:     if \"stream\" in log:\n234:         print(log[\"stream\"].strip())\n235: ```\n236: \n237: ---\n238: \n239: ## Implementation Timeline\n240: \n241: | Phase | Tasks | Status | Completion |\n242: |-------|-------|--------|------------|\n243: | Phase 1: Core Implementation | T1.1-T1.4 | Done | 100% |\n244: | Phase 2: Image Operations | T2.1-T2.5 | Done | 100% |\n245: | Phase 3: Unit Tests | T3.1-T3.7 | Done | 100% |\n246: | Phase 4: Integration | T4.1-T4.4 | Pending | 0% |\n247: \n248: **Total Progress: 75% Complete (15/20 tasks)**\n249: \n250: ---\n251: \n252: ## References\n253: \n254: - Design: `changes/AR-024/design.md`\n255: - Delta Spec: `changes/AR-024/delta-spec.md`\n256: - Docker SDK Python: https://docker-py.readthedocs.io/en/stable/\n257: - AR-021 — CLI build command (uses DockerService)\n258: - AR-022 — CLI publish command (uses DockerService.push_image)\n\n(End of file - total 258 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-024 — DockerService 封装 Tasks\n\n## Metadata\n\n| Item | Value |\n|------|-------|\n| AR | AR-024 — DockerService 封装 |\n| Module | `cmd/cli` |\n| Language | Python |\n| Size | M |\n| Design | [Stage ST-3 completed] |\n\n---\n\n## Task Checklist\n\n### Phase 1: Core Implementation (ST-1)\n\n- [x] **T1.1**: Implement `DockerService.__init__` with verbose flag and `_client=None`\n  - Purpose: Constructor initializes verbose flag and lazy client placeholder","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-024/tasks.md","time":{"start":1775876214698,"end":1775876214783}}}}
